article.headline: Lehigh 64, Wagner 59
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Austen Rowland scored 23 points and Earl Nurse scored 13 to lead Lehigh past Wagner 64-59 on Friday night. Wagner (3-7), which was led by Courtney Pritchard's 22 points, took a 32-27 halftime lead. But Lehigh (7-5) outscored Wagner in the second half behind 47 percent shooting from the floor, including five 3-pointers. Nigel Wyatte had 12 rebounds for Wagner, while Nick Monserez had nine for Lehigh. Wagner had 12 turnovers while Lehigh had only five.
